<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-09-01T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-09-01T00:00:00-05:00" n="1524" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1524">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.41/288.</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to Consul <persName type="to">Letcher</persName>.</hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#left">[No. 298.]</seg>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                        <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-09-01">
                                        <hi rend="italic">September 1, 1914</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: The Department has received your
                                dispatch No. 524 of August 6, 1914, in regard to the estate of the
                                late Mr. William S. Benton.</p>
                            <p>You are instructed to call the attention of General Villa to the fact
                                that a representative of the Benton estate has been continuously in
                                charge of the property and that the temporary tenants upon the
                                property should be informed by Villa that they are tenants of the
                                Benton estate and must pay their rents to the estate’s
                                representative.</p>
                            <p>I am [etc.]</p>
                            <closer>For the Secretary of State: <lb/>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilbur J. Carr</hi></signed>.</closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>